      "collected_data": "Sociodemographic data, Bath Ankylosing Spondylitis Metrology Index (BASM) for mobility (range: 0-10, lower scores = better mobility), PainDETECT for neuropathic pain (range: 0-38, higher scores = more severe pain), PAHCO (Physical Activity-related Health Competence, higher scores = better competence). Data collected at baseline, 3 months, and 6 months.",
      "key_outcomes_findings": "All three digital interventions significantly improved mobility (mean BASMI change: -0.6 to -0.7, p < 0.001) and reduced pain intensity (mean PainDETECT reduction: -4.6 to -6.6 points, p ≤ 0.006). PAHCO control competence increased significantly only in the ViViRA + coaching group (BL-6 month: +1.02, p = 0.013). No coaching strategy showed significant superiority over stand-alone digital therapy. Adherence was the same across groups after 3 months (2-3 weekly use of DHA).",
